Name: FRAGRANCE
Description: The word "fragrance" or "parfum" on the product label represents an undisclosed mixture of various scent chemicals and ingredients used as fragrance dispersants such as diethyl phthalate. Fragrance mixes have been associated with allergies, dermatitis, respiratory distress and potential effects on the reproductive system.

Name: GLYCERIN
Description: Glycerin (also called glycerol) is a naturally occurring alcohol compound and a component of many lipids. Glycerin may be of animal or vegetable origin. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as a byproduct of soap manufacture which typically uses animal fat.

Name: PHENOXYETHANOL
Description: Phenoxyethanol is a preservative used in cosmetics and personal care products.

Name: IRON OXIDES
Description: Iron oxides are inorganic chemicals used as colorants.

Name: TITANIUM DIOXIDE
Description: Titanium dioxide is an inorganic compound used in a range of body care products such as sunscreens and makeup. It appears to have low skin penetration but inhalation is a concern.

Name: TOCOPHEROL
Description: Tocopherols are a class of naturally occurring chemical compounds related to Vitamin E

Name: MICA
Description: Mica is a type of highly brittle silicate minerals with diverse chemical composition; typically used as a colorant.

Name: CITRIC ACID
Description: Citric acid is an alpha hydroxy acid used in personal care products to adjust the acidity or promote skin peeling and re-growth in the case of anti-aging products. Citric acid is naturally found in citric fruits and juices, providing the characteristic acidic taste.

Name: TOCOPHERYL ACETATE
Description: Tocopheryl acetate is a chemical compound that consists of acetic acid and tocopherol (vitamin E)

Name: DIMETHICONE
Description: Dimethicone (also called polymethylsiloxane) is a silicon-based polymer used as a lubricant and conditioning agent.

Name: SILICA, AMORPHOUS
Description: Silica is the most common constituent of sand. Fine silica, typically used in industrial applications and inhaled by workers, is associated with a wide range of disorders, particularly affecting the lungs and respiratory system. In cosmetics for skin use, regular sand presents little, if any risk to people. In contrast, for products that might be inhaled (such as a facial powder), silica particles are finely ground down and may be associated with respiratory toxicity.

Name: ETHYLHEXYLGLYCERIN
Description: Ethylhexylglycerin is a glyceryl ether used as a weak preservative and skin conditioning agent.

Name: CAPRYLYL GLYCOL
Description: Caprylyl glycol (1,2-octanediol) is used as a skin conditioning agent; has some antimicrobial activity.

Name: CAPRYLIC/ CAPRIC TRIGLYCERIDE
Description: Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride is a mixed triester of glycerin and caprylic and capric acids.

Name: BUTYROSPERMUM PARKII (SHEA) BUTTER
Description: Shea butter is a vegetable fat obtained from the fruit of a tree native to Africa, Butyrospermum parkii. Shea butter is primarily composed of fatty acids such as stearic and oleic acids.

Name: SODIUM CHLORIDE
Description: Sodium Chloride is an inorganic salt (also called table salt).

Name: SODIUM BENZOATE
Description: Sodium benzoate is a preservative commonly used in foods, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: DISODIUM EDTA
Description: EDTA (ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid) is a chelating agent, used to sequester and decrease the reactivity of metal ions that may be present in a product.

Name: BUTYLENE GLYCOL
Description: Butylene glycol (1.3-Butanediol) is a small organic alcohol used as solvent and conditioning agent.

Name: LIMONENE
Description: Limonene is a scent ingredient and solvent naturally ocurring in the rind of citrus fruit. Upon storage and exposure to sunlight and air, limonene degrades to various oxidation products which act as skin and respiratory irritants and sensitizers.

Name: LINALOOL
Description: Linalool is a terpene.

Name: COCOS NUCIFERA (COCONUT) OIL
Description: Coconut oil is extracted from the kernels of the seeds of coconot palm, Cocos nucifera.

Name: POTASSIUM SORBATE
Description: Potassium sorbate is a potassium salt of sorbic acid, a naturally occuringantimicrobial compound; used as a preservative

Name: HELIANTHUS ANNUUS (SUNFLOWER) OIL
Description: Sunflower oil is extracted from the seeds of the sunflower, Helianthus annuus.

Name: XANTHAN GUM
Description: Xanthan gum is a polysaccharide, a sugar-based polymer produced by bacteria; it is used as a viscosity agent in personal care products and foods.

Name: PANTHENOL
Description: Panthenol is a form of vitamin B5, used as a moisturizer and lubricating compound. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as a substance that can be of either animal or plant origin.

Name: ALOE BARBADENSIS (ALOE VERA) LEAF JUICE
Description: Aloe vera juice is produced from the succulent leaves of the aloe plant, Aloe barbadensis.

Name: CETEARYL ALCOHOL
Description: Cetearyl Alcohol is a mixture of cetyl and stearyl alcohols that can come from vegetable or synthetic sources.

Name: PROPYLENE GLYCOL
Description: Propylene glycol is a small organic alcohol commonly used as a skin conditioning agent. It has been associated with irritant and allergic contact dermatitis as well as contact urticaria in humans; these sensitization effects can be manifested at propylene glycol concentrations as low as 2%.

Name: SIMMONDSIA CHINENSIS (JOJOBA) SEED OIL
Description: Jojoba oil is extracted from seeds of the desert shrub, Simmondsia chinensis, native to California, Arizona and Mexico.

Name: CYCLOPENTASILOXANE
Description: Cyclopentasiloxane (cyclomethicone) is a silicon-based cyclic compound; may be associated with environmental toxicity.

Name: SODIUM HYALURONATE
Description: Sodium hyaluronate is the sodium salt of hyaluronic acid, a naturally occurring polysaccharide found in connective tissues such as cartilage. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as derived from animal sources.

Name: SODIUM HYDROXIDE
Description: Sodium Hydroxide is a highly caustic and reactive inorganic base.

Name: CETYL ALCOHOL
Description: Cetyl alcohol is a long chain organic alcohol; according to the PETA's Caring Consumer guide, this ingredient can be of either animal or plant origin.

Name: FD&C YELLOW 5 (CI 19140) ALUMINUM LAKE
Description: In industrial production of colorants, 'lake' is a term used for pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Some of the lake dyes may be derived from naturally occurring plant or animal ingredients but the vast majority of lakes is synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: COCAMIDOPROPYL BETAINE
Description: Cocamidopropyl betaine is a surfactant; it has been associated with irritation and allergic contact dermatitis, reactions that could be due to the ingredient itself or to impurities present in it, such as 3-dimethylaminopropylamine.

Name: CI 42090 (FD&C Blue No. 1 or D&C Blue No. 4) Aluminum Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, 'lake' is a term used for pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Some of the lake dyes may be derived from naturally occurring plant or animal ingredients but the vast majority of lakes is synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: STEARIC ACID
Description: Stearic acid is a naturally occurring fatty acid. It is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as a substance of animal origin, since stearic acid is primarily derived from rendered fat of farm and domestic animals.

Name: BENZYL ALCOHOL
Description: Benzyl alcohol is a naturally ocurring and synthetic ingredient used as solvent and preservative; has been associated with contact allergy.

Name: BEESWAX
Description: Beeswax is the purified wax from the honeycomb of the bee, Apis mellifera. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as a substance of animal origin.

Name: DISTEARDIMONIUM HECTORITE
Description: Disteardimonium hectorite is an ingredient based on naturally occurring clay mineral hectorite; this ingredient is used as a thickening agent.

Name: GLYCERYL MONOSTEARATE
Description: Glyceryl stearate is composed of naturally occuring lipid ingredients glycerol and stearic acid.

Name: TIN OXIDE
Description: Tin oxide is an inorganic oxide that is naturally found in mineral form.

Name: ISODODECANE
Description: Isododecane is a branched chain aliphatic hydrocarbon with 12 carbons; used as a solvent.

Name: CI 15850 (D&C Red No. 6 or 7) Aluminum Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: TALC
Description: Talc is a powdered native, hydrous magnesium silicate sometimes containing a small portion of aluminum silicate. Talc can be contaminated with asbestos fibers, posing risks for respiratory toxicity and cancer. Studies by the National Toxicology Panel demonstrated that cosmetic-grade talc free of asbestos is a form of magnesium silicate that also can be toxic and carcinogenic.

Name: CASTOR OIL
Description: Castor Oil is extracted from the seeds of Ricinus communis, a castor oil plant.

Name: ETHYLHEXYL PALMITATE
Description: Ethylhexyl Palmitate is an ester of 2-ethylhexyl alcohol and palmitic acid.

Name: CARBOMER
Description: Carbomer is a large polymeric chemical composed of acrylic acid monomers.

Name: CI 15850 (D&C Red No. 6 or 7)
Description: CI 15850 is classed chemically as a monoazo color.

Name: BHT
Description: Butylated hydroxytoluene (BHT) is a toluene-based ingredient used as a preservative in food and personal care products.

Name: SYNTHETIC FLUORPHLOGOPITE
Description: A synthetic mineral based on fluorine, aluminum and silicate; also known as synthetic fluorine mica; used as a bulking agent.

Name: FD&C Yellow 5 (CI 19140)
Description: FD&C Yellow 5 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum; this dye is FDA-approved for use in food, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: TRIMETHYLSILOXYSILICATE
Description: Trimethylsiloxysilicate is a silicon-based polymer.

Name: POLYETHYLENE
Description: Polyethylene is a polymer of ethylene monomers; may contain potentially toxic manufacturing contaminants such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: COPERNICIA CERIFERA (CARNAUBA) WAX
Description: Carnauba wax is extracted from the leaves of the carnauba palm, Copernicia cerifera, a plant native to Brazil.

Name: ULTRAMARINES
Description: Ultramarine (CI 77007 colorant) is a mineral-derived blue pigment composed of sodium, aluminum, silicate and sulfate; may be produced synthetically.

Name: PROPYLENE CARBONATE
Description: Propylene carbonate is a synthetic solvent.

Name: MICROCRYSTALLINE WAX (CERA MICROCRISTALLINA)
Description: Microcrystalline wax is a hydrocarbon wax derived from petroleum.

Name: OLEA EUROPAEA (OLIVE) OIL
Description: Olive oil is extracted from the reipe fruit of olive tree, Olea europaea.

Name: TETRASODIUM EDTA
Description: EDTA (ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid) is a chelating agent, used to sequester and decrease the reactivity of metal ions that may be present in a product.

Name: CI 42090 (FD&C Blue No. 1 or D&C Blue No. 4)
Description: FD&C Blue 1 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum; this dye is FDA-approved for use in food, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: CI 45410 (D&C Red No. 27 or 28) Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: POLYSORBATE-20
Description: Polysorbate 20 (Tween 20) is a surfactant and emulsifier used in cleaners and personal care products.

Name: ALCOHOL DENATURED
Description: Denatured alcohol is a mixture of ethanol (ethyl alcohol) with a denaturing agent. Ethanol is considered broadly toxic and linked to birth defects following excessive oral ingestion. Potential risks from ethanol in personal care products are significantly smaller than the health risks posed by the consumption of alcohol.

Name: OCTYLDODECANOL
Description: Octyldodecanol is a long chain fatty alcohol.

Name: CITRONELLOL
Description: Citronellol is a naturally ocurring scent ingredient derived from plants such as rose, geranium and lemongrass.

Name: TRIETHOXYCAPRYLYLSILANE
Description: Silicon-based ingredient; used as a binder.

Name: MANGANESE VIOLET
Description: Manganese violet is an inorganic salt ammonium manganese pyrophosphate used as a colorant.

Name: CARMINE
Description: Carmine is a red pigment/dye derived from insects native to South America and Mexico that live as parasites on cactus plants. Used as a colorant in food, cosmetics and textiles. Has been associated with severe allergic reactions. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as a substance of animal origin.

Name: EUPHORBIA CERIFERA (CANDELILLA) WAX
Description: Candelilla wax is extracted from Euphorbia cerifera, a shrub native to Mexico.

Name: HEXYLENE GLYCOL
Description: Hexylene glycol is a small molecular weight surfactant.

Name: GERANIOL
Description: Geraniol is a naturally occurring scent ingredient found in various essential oils such as rose oil and citronella oil.

Name: POLYBUTENE
Description: Polybutene is a polymer used as a plasticizer and viscosity agent.

Name: MINERAL OIL
Description: Mineral Oil is a liquid mixture of hydrocarbons obtained from petroleum.

Name: HEXYL CINNAMAL
Description: Hexyl cinnamal is a naturally occurring and synthetic scent ingredient; it is associated with allergic reactions.

Name: CAMELLIA SINENSIS (GREEN TEA) LEAF EXTRACT
Description: Green tea leaf extract is produced from the tea plant, Camelia sinensis.

Name: KAOLIN
Description: Kaolin is a clay minteral composed of hydrated aluminum silicate.

Name: LECITHIN
Description: Lecithin is a naturally ocurring lipid found in both plants and animals. According to the PETA's Caring Consumer guide, lecithin for com mercial purposes is most commonly obtain from eggs and soybeans.

Name: PERSEA GRATISSIMA (AVOCADO) OIL
Description: Avocado oil is extracted from the fruit of the avocado tree, Persea americana or Persea gratissima.

Name: ARGANIA SPINOSA (ARGAN) KERNEL OIL
Description: Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil is a fixed oil expressed from the kernels of the African tree, Argania spinosa.

Name: ETHANOL
Description: Ethanol or ethyl alcohol is considered broadly toxic and linked to birth defects following excessive oral ingestion. Potential risks from ethanol in personal care products are significantly smaller than the health risks posed by the consumption of alcoholic beverages.

Name: THEOBROMA CACAO (COCOA) SEED BUTTER
Description: Cocoa Butter is extracted from the roasted seeds of Theobroma cacao, a tree native to the Americas.

Name: ALUMINUM HYDROXIDE
Description: Aluminum hydroxide, also known as hydrated alumina, is a form of aluminum used as a colorant.

Name: METHYLISOTHIAZOLINONE
Description: Methylisothiazolinone is a widely-used preservative; has been associated with allergic reactions. Lab studies on the brain cells of mammals also suggest that methylisothiazolinone may be neurotoxic.

Name: SQUALANE
Description: Squalane is a naturally occuring lipid in both plants and animals. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as primarily derived from animals, especially shark liver oil.

Name: FLAVOR
Description: Flavor is a term used by cosmetic manufacturers for substances or combination of substances added to a cosmetic product to produce or to mask a particular flavor.

Name: ASCORBYL PALMITATE (VITAMIN C PALMITATE)
Description: Ascorbyl Palmitate is a compound composed of of Ascorbic Acid (Vitamin C) and palmitic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: HYDROGENATED POLYISOBUTENE
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic polymer used as a skin conditioning agent.

Name: ROSMARINUS OFFICINALIS (ROSEMARY) LEAF EXTRACT
Description: Rosemary leaf extract is produced from the leaves of the Rosmarinus officinalis plant.

Name: STEARYL ALCOHOL
Description: Stearyl alcohol is a compound produced from stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: SODIUM LAURETH SULFATE
Description: Sodium Laureth Sulfate is and ingredient derived from ethoxylated lauryl alcohol and used as a surfactant; may be contaminated with potentially toxic manufacturing impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: BENZYL SALICYLATE
Description: Benzyl Salicylate is an ester of benzyl alcohol and salicylic acid; this ingredient has been associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: ALLANTOIN
Description: Allantoin is a naturally ocurring nitrogenous compound used as a skin conditioning agent.

Name: METHYLCHLOROISOTHIAZOLINONE
Description: Methylchloroisothiazolinone is a widely-used preservative; has been associated with allergic reactions.

Name: METHYLPARABEN
Description: Methylparaben is in the paraben family of preservatives used by the food, pharmaceutical, and personal care product industries. Parabens mimic estrogen and can act as potential hormone (endocrine) system disruptors.

Name: CHAMOMILLA RECUTITA (MATRICARIA) FLOWER EXTRACT
Description: Extract of the camomile (Chamomilla Recutita) flowers.

Name: ALOE BARBADENSIS (ALOE VERA) LEAF EXTRACT
Description: Aloe vera leaf extract is produced from the succulent leaves of the aloe plant, Aloe barbadensis

Name: SYNTHETIC WAX
Description: Synthetic wax is a hydrocarbon wax produced from fossil fuel materials such as natural gas.

Name: TITANIUM DIOXIDE (sunscreen grade)
Description: Titanium dioxide has a long history of use as a sunscreen agent. Nano TiO2 offers greater sun protection than larger titanium particles. Comparatively little is known regarding potential health effects of nanoparticles. They do not penetrate healthy skin, and thus appear to pose a low health risk in lotions. Inhalation of powders and sprays is a concern.

Name: CITRAL
Description: Citral is a naturally occurring scent ingredient; manufactured synthetically on a large scale; associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: ACRYLATES COPOLYMER
Description: Acrylates copolymer is composed of acrylic acid and methacrylic acid building blocks.

Name: PRUNUS AMYGDALUS DULCIS (SWEET ALMOND) OIL
Description: Almond oil is extracted from the seed kernels of the sweet almond plant, Prunus Amygdalus Dulcis.

Name: GLYCINE SOJA (SOYBEAN) OIL
Description: Soybean oil is obtained from Glycine Soja plant; this ingredient primarily consists of triglycerides of oleic, linoleic, linolenic and saturated acids.

Name: NYLON-12
Description: Nylon-12 is a type of synthetic polymer known as polyamide

Name: NIACINAMIDE
Description: Niacinamide is a form of vitamin B3(niacin), a water-soluble vitamin; used in cosmetics and personal care products as a conditioning agent.

Name: CETYL PEG/ PPG-10/ 1 DIMETHICONE
Description: This skin conditioning agent is a synthetic chemical consisting of dimethicone, a silicon-based polymer and polyethylene glycol (PEG)-polypropylene glycol (PPG) polymer. May be contaminated with potentially toxic manufacturing impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: SODIUM CITRATE
Description: Cosmetic manufacturers use sodium citrate to adjust the acidity of a product. Citrate, in the form of citric acid, is also found in citric fruits and juices.

Name: PHENYL TRIMETHICONE
Description: Phenyl trimethicone is a silicon-based polymer.

Name: ALUMINA
Description: Alumina is the name used for inorganic compound aluminium oxide.

Name: BISMUTH OXYCHLORIDE
Description: Bismuth oxychloride is a naturally ocurring mineral used as a makeup colorant that provides an iridescent (shiny) effect.

Name: LAVANDULA ANGUSTIFOLIA (LAVENDER) OIL
Description: A volatile oil obtained from Lavendula officinalis, a common medicinal plant; can act as an allergen.

Name: COUMARIN
Description: Coumarin is a naturally occurring and synthetically produced scent chemical; associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: GUAR HYDROXYPROPYLTRIMONIUM CHLORIDE
Description: Guar Hydroxypropyltrimonium Chloride is a quaternary ammonium derivative of guar gum; used in hair conditioning products.

Name: PENTYLENE GLYCOL
Description: Pentylene glycol is a synthetic, low molecular weight solvent and skin-conditioning agent.

Name: D&C Red No. 33 (CI 17200)
Description: D&C Red 33 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum or coal tar sources; this dye is FDA-approved for use in pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: BORON NITRIDE
Description: Boron nitride is a synthetic boron-based inorganic compound used in cosmetics and personal care products to increase adherence and act as oil absorbent.

Name: BIS-DIGLYCERYL POLYACYLADIPATE-2
Description: This ingredient is a lipid-based synthetic skin-conditioning agent.

Name: PETROLATUM
Description: Petrolatum is a semisolid mixture of hydrocarbons obtained from petroleum.

Name: SILICA DIMETHYL SILYLATE
Description: Silica dimethyl silylate is a silica-based synthetic derivative.

Name: CHLORPHENESIN
Description: Chlorphenesin is a synthetic preservative.

Name: DIISOSTEARYL MALATE
Description: Diisostearyl Malate is a diester of Isostearyl Alcohol (q.v.) and Malic Acid (q.v.).

Name: ISOPROPYL ALCOHOL
Description: Isopropyl alcohol is a common solvent.

Name: BENZYL BENZOATE
Description: Benzyl benzoate is used as solvent and preservative; associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: SODIUM DEHYDROACETATE
Description: Sodium dehydroacetate is an antimicrobial ingredient used as preservative.

Name: OZOKERITE
Description: Ozokerite is a hydrocarbon wax derived from mineral sources or from petroleum.

Name: CETRIMONIUM CHLORIDE
Description: Cetrimonium chloride is a quaternary ammonium compound used as a preservative.

Name: PROPYLPARABEN
Description: Propylparaben is in the paraben family of preservatives used by the food, pharmaceutical, and personal care product industries. Parabens mimic estrogen and can act as potential hormone (endocrine) system disruptors.

Name: HYDROXYETHYLCELLULOSE
Description: Hydroxyethylcellulose is a modified cellulose polymer; used as a gelling and thickening agent.

Name: CALCIUM SODIUM BOROSILICATE
Description: Calcium sodium borosilicate is a glass-type material used as a bulking agent.

Name: SORBITOL
Description: Sorbitol (glucitol) is a type of sugar alcohol used as a thickener and a skin conditioning agent.

Name: FD&C Yellow No. 6 (CI 15985) Aluminum Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: BEHENTRIMONIUM CHLORIDE
Description: Behentrimonium chloride is a quaternary ammonium salt used as a preservative.

Name: BENZOIC ACID
Description: Benzoic acid is a naturally occurring and synthetically produced substance; it is used in food and cosmetics as a preservative.

Name: MAGNESIUM SULFATE
Description: Magnesium sulfate (Epson salt) is an inorganic salt; found in sea water and in mineral deposits.

Name: ZINC STEARATE
Description: Zinc Stearate is a zinc salt of stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: DIPROPYLENE GLYCOL
Description: Dipropylene glycol is a small molecular weight synthetic solvent.

Name: DIMETHICONE/ VINYL DIMETHICONE CROSSPOLYMER
Description: Dimethicone/Vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer is a copolymer of dimethylpolysiloxanecrosslinked with vinyl dimethylpolysiloxane.

Name: LACTIC ACID
Description: Lactic acid is an alpha hydroxy acid; naturally produced in the process of bacterial fermentation, for example milk fermentation. Lactic acid is frequently used as an exfoliant and in anti-wrinkle products.

Name: FERRIC FERROCYANIDE
Description: Ferric ferrocyanide is an iron-based inorganic colorant also known as Prussian blue; one of the first synthetic pigments.

Name: ISOPROPYL MYRISTATE
Description: Isopropyl Myristate is composed of of isopropyl alcohol and myristic acid, a common, naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: TRIETHANOLAMINE
Description: Triethanolamine is a strongly alkaline substance used as surfactant and pH adjusting chemical.

Name: C12-15 ALKYL BENZOATE
Description: This ingredient is composed of benzoic acid and long-chain (C12-15) alcohols .

Name: DECYL GLUCOSIDE
Description: Decyl glucoside is a glucose-based surfactant commonly used in shampoos and body washes.

Name: CALCIUM ALUMINUM BOROSILICATE
Description: Calcium aluminum borosilicate is a glass-type material used as a bulking agent.

Name: SORBIC ACID
Description: Sorbic acid is a naturally occuring and synthetically produced compound used as a preservative.

Name: VITIS VINIFERA (GRAPE) SEED OIL
Description: Grape seed oil is obtained from the seeds of grape plant, Vitis vinifera.

Name: PEG-40 HYDROGENATED CASTOR OIL
Description: PEG-40 hydrogenated castor oil is a polyethylene glycol derivative of castor oil; may be contaminated with potentially toxic impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: GLYCERYL CAPRYLATE
Description: Glyceryl Caprylate is a monoester of glycerin and caprylic acid.

Name: ASCORBIC ACID (VITAMIN C)
Description: Ascorbic acid (Vitamin C) is a naturally occurring antioxidant.

Name: PARAFFIN
Description: Paraffin is a solid mixture of hydrocarbons obtained from petroleum.

Name: DIMETHICONE CROSSPOLYMER
Description: This ingredient is a silicon-based polymer (dimethicone) modified with hydrocarbon side chains in the C3-C20 size range.

Name: CARTHAMNUS TINCTORIUS (SAFFLOWER) OIL
Description: Safflower seed oil is obtained from the seed of Carthamus tinctorius; this ingredient consists primarily of the triglycerides of linoleic acid.

Name: ACRYLATES/ C10-30 ALKYL ACRYLATE CROSSPOLYMER
Description: This ingredient is a polymer of actylic acid and related chemicals.

Name: CHROMIUM OXIDE GREENS
Description: Chromium oxide is a mineral pigment, Cr2O3, used as a colorant in a variety of products. This ingredient contains trivalent chromium, a form of chromium that functions as an essential trace element in human metabolism.

Name: PEG-100 STEARATE
Description: PEG-100 Stearate is a polyethylene glycol ester of stearic acid.

Name: DIMETHICONOL
Description: Dimethiconol is a silicon-based polymer.

Name: SODIUM LAURYL SULFATE
Description: Sodium lauryl sulfate is the sodium salt of lauryl sulfate.

Name: RETINYL PALMITATE (VITAMIN A PALMITATE)
Description: Retinyl palmitate is an ingredient composed of palmitic acid and retinol (Vitamin A). Data from an FDA study indicate that retinyl palmitate, when applied to the skin in the presence of sunlight, may speed the development of skin tumors and lesions. FDA, Norwegian and German health agencies have raised a concern that daily skin application of vitamin A creams may contribute to excessive vitamin A intake for pregnant women and other populations.

Name: DEHYDROACETIC ACID
Description: Dehydroacetic acid is a synthetic preservative.

Name: GLYCOL DISTEARATE
Description: Glycol distearate is a compound based on stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: ISONONYL ISONONANOATE
Description: Synthetic skin conditioning agent.

Name: POLYHYDROXYSTEARIC ACID
Description: Polyhydroxystearic Acid is a polymer of Hydroxystearic Acid (q.v.)

Name: HYDROXYCITRONELLAL
Description: Hydroxycitronellal is a common scent ingredient; produced synthetically from naturally occurring scent chemical citronellal.

Name: ALPHA-ISOMETHYL IONONE
Description: Ionones are a group of naturally occurring and synthetically produced scent chemicals.

Name: MENTHA PIPERITA (PEPPERMINT) OIL
Description: Peppermint oil is a volatile oil obtained from the plant Mentha piperita.

Name: CALENDULA OFFICINALIS (POT MARIGOLD) FLOWER EXTRACT
Description: Extract of the calendula (Calendula officinalis) flowers.

Name: PEG-10 DIMETHICONE
Description: PEG-10 Dimethicone is a polyethylene glycol derivative of Dimethicone (q.v.) containing anaverage of 10 moles of ethylene oxide.

Name: OCTINOXATE
Description: This common sunscreen ingredient is shown to have hormone-mimicking effects on laboratory animals. This chemical is found in humans, including mothers' milk samples.

Name: SODIUM BICARBONATE
Description: Sodium bicarbonate (baking soda) is an inorganic salt

Name: PALMITIC ACID
Description: Palmitic acid is a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: POLYSORBATE-60
Description: Polysorbate 60 (Tween-60) is a sorbitol-based emulsifier and surfactant.

Name: LAUROYL LYSINE
Description: Lauroyl lysine is a derivative of lauric acid and lysine, a naturally occurring amino acid.

Name: MAGNESIUM STEARATE
Description: Magnesium stearate is a magnesium salt of stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: SODIUM PCA
Description: Sodium PCA is a derivative of naturally occurring amino acid proline; it is used as a conditioning agent.

Name: POLYMETHYLSILSESQUIOXANE
Description: Polymethylsilsesquioxane is a polymer formed by the hydrolysis and condensation ofmethyltrimethoxysilane.

Name: LILIAL
Description: Lilial (butylphenyl methylpropanal) is a synthetic scent ingredient; associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: CI 45410 (D&C Red No. 27 or 28)
Description: D&C Red 27 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum or coal tar sources; this dye is FDA-approved for use in pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: HYDROGENATED CASTOR OIL
Description: This ingredient is produced by hydrogenation of Ricinus communis (Castor) seed oil.

Name: POLYQUATERNIUM-10
Description: Polyquaternium-10 is a synthetic polymeric.

Name: METHICONE
Description: Methicone is a linear silicone-based polymer.

Name: TRIBEHENIN
Description: Tribehenin is composed of glycerin and behenic acid, a naturally-occurring long-chain fatty acid.

Name: FD&C Red No. 40 (CI 16035) Aluminum Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: CYCLOHEXASILOXANE
Description: Cyclohexasiloxane is a cyclic silicon-based polymer.

Name: SORBITAN ISOSTEARATE
Description: This ingredient is a surfactant composed of sorbitol and isostearic acid, a fatty acid.

Name: AMINOMETHYL PROPANOL
Description: This ingredient is a small molecular weight buffering agent.

Name: ALUMINUM STARCH OCTENYLSUCCINATE
Description: This ingredient is an aluminum salt of chemically modified starch.

Name: POLYQUATERNIUM-7
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic polymer based on quaternary ammonium compounds.

Name: MALTODEXTRIN
Description: Maltodextrin is a saccharide material obtained by hydrolysis of starch.

Name: SIMMONDSIA CHINENSIS (JOJOBA) ESTERS
Description: Jojoba Esters is a complex mixture of esters produced by the transesterification/interesterification of Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Oil (q.v.), Hydrogenated Jojoba Oil (q.v.), or amixture of the two.

Name: COCO-GLUCOSIDE
Description: Coco-glucoside is a surfactant produced by chemical reaction between glucose and coconut oil-derived ingredients.

Name: OCTYLDODECYL STEAROYL STEARATE
Description: Octyldodecyl stearoyl stearate is a lipid-based synthetic skin conditioning agent.

Name: ISOHEXADECANE
Description: Isohexadecane is a branched chain hydrocarbon with 16 carbons; it is a component of petroleum; used as a skin-conditioning agent in personal care products.

Name: CUCUMIS SATIVUS (CUCUMBER) FRUIT EXTRACT
Description: Extract of the fruit of the cucumber, Cucumis sativus.

Name: MELALEUCA ALTERNIFOLIA (TEA TREE) LEAF OIL
Description: This ingredient is distilled from the leaves of Tea Tree, Melaleuca alternifolia, a shrub native to New Zealand.

Name: PENTAERYTHRITYL TETRAISOSTEARATE
Description: Pentaerythrityl tetraisostearate is a synthetic lipid-based ingredient used as a skin conditioning agent.

Name: SODIUM COCOYL ISETHIONATE
Description: Sodium cocoyl isethionate is a surfactant based on fatty acids from coconut oil and isoethionic acid, a type of sulfonic acid.

Name: PVP
Description: PVP (polyvinylpyrrolidone) is a water-soluble synthetic polymer.

Name: FD&C Red No. 40 (CI 16035)
Description: FD&C Red 40 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum; this dye is FDA-approved for use in food, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: COCO-CAPRYLATE/ CAPRATE
Description: Coco-Caprylate/Caprate is a mixture of esters of Coconut Alcohol (q.v.) with Caprylic Acid(q.v.) and Capric Acid (q.v.).

Name: ZEA MAYS (CORN) STARCH
Description: Zea Mays (Corn) Starch is a starch obtained from corn.

Name: MANGIFERA INDICA (MANGO) SEED BUTTER
Description: Mango seed butter is a fat obtained from the seed of Mangifera indica.

Name: ISOPROPYL PALMITATE
Description: Isopropyl Palmitate is an ester of isopropyl alcohol and palmitic acid.

Name: SALICYLIC ACID
Description: Salicylic acid is a naturally occuring and synthetically produced beta hydroxy acid used in skin treatment products.

Name: METHYL METHACRYLATE CROSSPOLYMER
Description: Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer is a copolymer of methyl methacrylate crosslinked withglycol dimethacrylate.

Name: AMODIMETHICONE
Description: Amodimethicone is a silicon-based polymer.

Name: AVOBENZONE
Description: This common sunscreen ingredient offers protection from UVA rays. Sunlight can cause this ingredient to break down and lose its effectiveness for skin protection. Photodegredation is delayed by mixing avobenzone with stabilizing chemicals.

Name: ARGININE
Description: Arginine is a naturally occurring amino acid.

Name: SYNTHETIC BEESWAX
Description: Synthetic Beeswax is a wax synthetically derived to be generally indistinguishable from naturalbeeswax with regard to composition and properties. It consists chiefly of a mixture of esters of even-numbered, straight chain acids and alcohols co ntaining 16-36 carbon atoms.

Name: HYDRATED SILICA
Description: Hydrated silica is a form of silicon dioxide (sand).

Name: OCTISALATE
Description: Octisalate is a sunscreen ingredient with a generally good safety profile. It can stabilize avobenzone and result in longer-lasting sun protection.

Name: CELLULOSE GUM
Description: This ingredient is a chemically-treated cellulose derivative.

Name: MENTHOL
Description: Menthol is a scent ingredient naturally found in peppermin oil; also manufactured synthetically on a large scale.

Name: BETAINE
Description: Betaine is a zwitterion (inner salt).

Name: ALUMINUM POWDER
Description: Aluminum Powder is a metallic substance composed of finely ground particles of aluminum; used as a colorant.

Name: BISABOLOL
Description: Bisabolol is a scent ingredient naturally occurring in camomile.

Name: GLUCONOLACTONE
Description: Gluconolactone is a lactone.

Name: D&C RED NO. 30 (CI 73360) LAKE
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: IODOPROPYNYL BUTYLCARBAMATE
Description: Iodopropynyl butylcarbamate is used as a preservative in cosmetic formulations; it is acutely toxic by inhalation and should not be used in products that can be aerosolized or inhaled.

Name: SORBITAN SESQUIOLEATE
Description: Sorbitan sesquioleate is a surfactant and emulsifier based on sorbitol and modified oleic acid; may be a contact allergen.

Name: COCAMIDE MEA
Description: Cocamide MEA is a compound synthesized from coconut oils and ethanolamine.

Name: ROSMARINUS OFFICINALIS (ROSEMARY) LEAF OIL
Description: Rosemary leaf oil is extracted from the flowering tops and leaves of the Rosmarinus officinalis plant.

Name: MAGNESIUM ALUMINUM SILICATE
Description: Magnesium Aluminum Silicate is a complex silicate refined from naturally occurring minerals.

Name: SODIUM SACCHARIN
Description: Saccharin is an aritifical sweetener benzoic sulfimide.

Name: CETEARETH-20
Description: Ceteareth-20 is the polyethylene glycol ether of cetearyl alcohol; may contain potentially toxic impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: CERESIN
Description: Ceresin is a waxy mixture of hydrocarbons obtained by purification of ozokerite, a naturally occurring mineral wax.

Name: MACADAMIA TERNIFOLIA (MACADAMIA) SEED OIL
Description: Oil obtained from the nuts of Macadamia ternifolia.

Name: ETHYL ACETATE
Description: Ethyl acetate is a widely used synthetic solvent.

Name: DMDM HYDANTOIN (FORMALDEHYDE RELEASER)
Description: DMDM hydantoin is an antimicrobial formaldehyde releaser preservative. People exposed to such formaldehyde-releasing ingredients may develop a formaldehyde allergy or an allergy to the ingredient itself and its decomposition products. In the U.S., approximately 20% of cosmetics and personal care products contain a formaldehyde-releaser and the frequency of contact allergy to these ingredients is much higher among Americans compared to studies in Europe.

Name: POLYISOBUTENE
Description: Polyisobutene is a synthetic polymer of isobutylene; used as a film-forming agent.

Name: TRIDECYL TRIMELLITATE
Description: Tridecyl Trimellitate is a triester of Tridecyl Alcohol (q.v.) and trimellitic acid.

Name: ZINC OXIDE
Description: Zinc Oxide is an inorganic oxide used as a colorant and sunscreen agent.

Name: EUGENOL
Description: Eugenol is a naturally occuring scent chemical found in clove oil; also manufactured synthetically. Has been associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: SODIUM PHYTATE
Description: Sodium Phytate is a complex sodium salt of Phytic Acid (q.v.).

Name: BUTYL ACETATE
Description: Butyl acetate is a naturally occurring and synthetically produced solvent.

Name: SILICA SILYLATE
Description: Silica Silylate is a hydrophobic silica derivative where some of the hydroxyl groups on thesurface of the fumed silica have been replaced by trimethylsiloxyl groups.

Name: CANNABIS SATIVA (HEMP) SEED OIL
Description: Hemp oil is extracted from the seeds of the Cannabis sativa plant.

Name: FD&C Yellow No. 6 (CI 15985)
Description: FD&C Yellow 6 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum; this dye is FDA-approved for use in food, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: NITROCELLULOSE
Description: Nitrocellulose is a highly flammable ingredient obtained by treating cellulose with nitric acid; used as a film-forming agent in cosmetics and personal care products.

Name: LAURYL GLUCOSIDE
Description: This ingredient is a sugar- and lipid-based surfactant.

Name: POLYSORBATE-80
Description: Polysorbate 80 is a surfactant and emulsifier used in cleaners and personal care products.

Name: TETRAHEXYLDECYL ASCORBATE
Description: Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate is an ester of Hexyldecanol (q.v.) and Ascorbic Acid (q.v.)..

Name: SORBITAN OLIVATE
Description: Sorbitan olivate is a surfactant based on olive oil and sorbitol.

Name: POTASSIUM HYDROXIDE
Description: Potassium Hydroxide is a caustic inorganic base.

Name: CI 45380 (D&C Red No. 21 or 22) Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: FERRIC AMMONIUM FERROCYANIDE
Description: Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide is an iron-based inorganic salt used as a colorant.

Name: POLYGLYCERYL-3 DIISOSTEARATE
Description: Polyglyceryl-3 Diisostearate is a diester of Isostearic Acid (q.v.) and Polyglycerin-3 (q.v.).

Name: GLYCERYL STEARATE SE
Description: Glyceryl Stearate SE (self-emulsifying) is a lipid used as surfactant and emulsifying agent.

Name: TRIETHYL CITRATE
Description: Triethyl Citrate is a triester of ethyl alcohol and citric acid.

Name: POLYGLYCERYL-4 ISOSTEARATE
Description: This ingredient is a lipid-based synthetic skin conditioning agent.

Name: COCAMIDOPROPYL HYDROXYSULTAINE
Description: Synthetic skin and hair conditioning agent.

Name: HYDROGENATED VEGETABLE OIL
Description: Ingredient produced by hydrogenation of vegetable oil.

Name: D&C Red No. 33 (CI 17200) Lake
Description: In industrial production of colorants, the term 'lake' is applied to pigments or dyes that are precipitated with metal salts such as aluminum, calcium, barium, or others. Most lake pigments are synthetically produced from coal tar or petroleum.

Name: PYRUS MALUS (APPLE) FRUIT EXTRACT
Description: Extract of apples, fruit of Pyrus malus tree.

Name: ZINC OXIDE (sunscreen grade)
Description: Sunscreens with zinc oxide usually contain nanoparticles. Zinc oxide in sunscreen offers UVA protection. Nanoparticle zinc oxide in sunscreen does not penetrate healthy skin, and thus appear to pose a low health risk in lotions. Inhalation of powders and sprays is a concern, however.

Name: STEARALKONIUM HECTORITE
Description: This ingredient is produced from hectorite, a naturally occurring mineral and a principal constituent of bentonite clay.

Name: GLYCERYL OLEATE
Description: Glyceryl Oleate is composed of glycerin and oleic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: CAFFEINE
Description: Caffeine is a heterocyclic organic compound.

Name: ISOBUTANE
Description: isobutane is a hydrocarbon gas; used as a propellant in aerosolized products.

Name: PEG/ PPG-18/ 18 DIMETHICONE
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic chemical consisting of dimethicone, a silicon-based polymer and polyethylene glycol (PEG)-polypropylene glycol (PPG) polymer. May be contaminated with potentially toxic manufacturing impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: BEHENYL ALCOHOL
Description: Behenyl alcohol is a saturated fatty alcohol as an emollient, emulsifier, and thickener.

Name: GLYCYRRHIZA GLABRA (LICORICE) ROOT EXTRACT
Description: Glycyrrhiza Glabra (Licorice) Root Extract is an extract of the root of the licorice, Glycyrrhizaglabra.

Name: SESAMUM INDICUM (SESAME) SEED OIL
Description: Oil of the sesame (Sesamum indicum) seeds.

Name: SODIUM C14-16 OLEFIN SULFONATE
Description: Sodium C14-16 Olefin Sulfonate is a mixture of long chain sulfonate salts prepared bysulfonation of C14-16 alpha olefins. It consists chiefly of sodium alkene sulfonates and sodiumhydroxyalkane sulfonates.

Name: CAPRYLYL METHICONE
Description: Caprylyl Methicone is a siloxane polymer.

Name: FD&C Red No. 4 (CI 14700)
Description: FD&C Red 4 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum; this dye is FDA-approved for use in food, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: LIMNANTHES ALBA (MEADOWFOAM) SEED OIL
Description: Oil extracted from the seeds of the meadowfoam plant, Limnanthes alba.

Name: ACETYL TRIBUTYL CITRATE
Description: Acetyl Tributyl Citrate is an aliphatic ester.

Name: POLYMETHYL METHACRYLATE
Description: Polymethyl methacyrlate is a synthetic polymer.

Name: STEARAMIDOPROPYL DIMETHYLAMINE
Description: Stearamidopropyl dimethylamine is a lipid-based conditioning agent.

Name: LAURETH-7
Description: Laureth-7 is a polyethylene glycol-based surfactant; may contain potentially toxic impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: HYDROGENATED LECITHIN
Description: Hydrogenated Lecithin is an end-product of the controlled hydrogenation of Lecithin (q.v.).

Name: SUCROSE
Description: A naturally occurring disaccharide (table sugar).

Name: POLYETHYLENE TEREPHTHALATE
Description: Polyethylene terephthalate is a synthetic plastic polymer used as a film-forming agent.

Name: HELIANTHUS ANNUUS (SUNFLOWER) SEED WAX
Description: Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Wax is a wax obtained from the seed of the sunflower, Helianthus annuus.

Name: TRIHYDROXYSTEARIN
Description: This ingredient is a lipid composed of glycerin and hydroxystearic acid, a type of fatty acid.

Name: BEHENTRIMONIUM METHOSULFATE
Description: Behentrimonium is a quaternary ammonium salt.

Name: CITRUS AURANTIUM BERGAMIA (BERGAMOT) FRUIT OIL
Description: Volatile oil obtained from the cirtus fruit of bergamot, Citrus aurantium bergamia.

Name: CHARCOAL POWDER
Description: Charcoal Powder is a dried, carbonaceous material obtained from the heating of organicsubstances.

Name: SEA SALT
Description: Sea salt is a mixture of inorganic salts derived from sea water or from inland bodies of saltwater.

Name: STYRENE/ ACRYLATES COPOLYMER
Description: Styrene/Acrylates Copolymer is a polymer of styrene and a monomer consisting of acrylicacid, methacrylic acid or one of their simple esters.

Name: HDI/ TRIMETHYLOL HEXYLLACTONE CROSSPOLYMER
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic polymer.

Name: CITRUS AURANTIUM DULCIS (ORANGE) OIL
Description: Volatile oil expressed from the fresh peel of the orange fruit.

Name: STEARALKONIUM BENTONITE
Description: This ingredient is a reaction product of bentonite, a type of aluminosilicate clay, and stearalkonium chloride, a quaternary amine surfactant and antimicrobial agent.

Name: ALGAE/SEAWEED/KELP EXTRACT (species unspecified)
Description: Algae Extract is an unspecified botanical extract of different species of algae (can vary between manufacturers).

Name: COCOS NUCIFERA (COCONUT) EXTRACT
Description: Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Extract is an extract of the meat of the coconut, Cocos nucifera.

Name: HYALURONIC ACID
Description: Hyaluronic Acid is a natural polysaccharide found in connective tissues such as cartilage.

Name: HYDROGENATED POLYDECENE
Description: Hydrogenated Polydecene is an end-product of the controlled hydrogenation of Polydecene(q.v.).

Name: HONEY
Description: Honey is a saccharic secretion gathered and stored by honey bees, Apis mellifera.

Name: BARIUM SULFATE
Description: Barium Sulfate is an inorganic salt.

Name: PEG-8
Description: The term "PEG" (polyethylene glycol) is used for synthetic polymers of ethylene oxide; these polymers may be contamated with potentially toxic manufacturing impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: PEG-150 DISTEARATE
Description: PEG-150 Distearate is a polyethylene glycol diester of stearic acid.

Name: VANILLA PLANIFOLIA (VANILLA) FRUIT EXTRACT
Description: This ingredient is an extract of the fruit (bean) of the vanilla plant, Vanilla planifolia.

Name: EUCALYPTUS GLOBULUS (EUCALYPTUS) LEAF OIL
Description: Eucalyptus Globulus Leaf Oil is a volatile oil obtained from the fresh leaves of Eucalyptusglobulus and other species of Eucalyptus.

Name: POLYGLYCERYL-2 TRIISOSTEARATE
Description: Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate is a triester of isostearic acid and Diglycerin (q.v.).

Name: AMYLCINNAMALDEHYDE
Description: Amyl cinnamal is a synthetically produced scent ingredient; has been associated with allergies and contact dermatitis.

Name: OCTOCRYLENE
Description: Octocrylene is a common sunscreen ingredient. It may cause allergic skin reactions in sensitive individuals.

Name: PALMITOYL TRIPEPTIDE-1
Description: Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1 is a reaction product of palmitic acid and Tripeptide-1 (q.v.).

Name: LAURETH-4
Description: Laureth-4 is a synthetic polymer composed of lauryl alcohol and PEG (polyethylene glycol). Due to the presence of PEG, this ingredient may contain potentially toxic manufacturing impurities such as 1,4-dioxane.

Name: SODIUM LACTATE
Description: Sodium Lactate is a sodium salt of lactic acid.

Name: CETEARYL OLIVATE
Description: Cetearyl olivate is composed of cetearyl alcohol and fatty acids derived from olive oil.

Name: ETHYLPARABEN
Description: Ethylparaben is in the paraben family of preservatives used by the food, pharmaceutical, and personal care product industries. Parabens mimic estrogen and can act as potential hormone (endocrine) system disruptors.

Name: TRIETHYLHEXANOIN
Description: Triethylhexanoin is a triester of glycerin and 2-ethylhexanoic acid.

Name: CETEARYL GLUCOSIDE
Description: Cetearyl glucoside is a surfactant and emulsifier produced from natural or synthetic ingredients.

Name: ETHYLENE/ PROPYLENE/ STYRENE COPOLYMER
Description: Ethylene/Propylene/Styrene Copolymer is a polymer of ethylene, propylene and styrenemonomers that has been terminated by hydrogenation.

Name: POLYSILICONE-11
Description: Polysilicone-11 is a crosslinked siloxane rubber formed by the reaction of vinyl-terminatedsiloxane and methylhydroxydimethyl siloxane in the presence of cyclomethicone.

Name: TREHALOSE
Description: Trehalose is a disaccharide.

Name: VP/ HEXADECENE COPOLYMER
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic polymer based on hexadecene, a hydrcarbon obtain from petroleum, and vinylpyrrolidone

Name: PANAX GINSENG (GINSENG) ROOT EXTRACT
Description: Extract of the root of ginseng plant, Panax ginseng.

Name: PHENETHYL ALCOHOL
Description: Phenethyl Alcohol is an aromatic alcohol.

Name: Ext. D&C Violet No. 2 (CI 60730)
Description: Ext. (external) D&C Violet 2 is a synthetic colorant.

Name: HYDROXYETHYL ACRYLATE/ SODIUM ACRYLOYLDIMETHYL TAURATE COPOLYMER
Description: Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer is a copolymer of sodiumhydroxyethyl acrylate and acryloyldimethyl taurate monomers.

Name: SULISOBENZONE
Description: Sulisobenzone (benzophenone-4) is a sunscreen ingredient; can cause skin and eye irritation. Does not penetrate the skin to a large degree, but enhances the ability of other chemicals to penetrate.

Name: ADIPIC ACID/ NEOPENTYL GLYCOL/ TRIMELLITIC ANHYDRIDE COPOLYMER
Description: Adipic Acid/Neopentyl Glycol/Trimellitic Anhydride Copolymer is a copolymer of adipic acid, neopentyl glycol and trimellitic anhydride monomers.

Name: CHROMIUM HYDROXIDE GREEN
Description: Chromium hydroxide is a mineral colorant Cr(OH)3 used in a variety of products. This ingredient contains trivalent chromium, a form of chromium that functions as an essential trace element in human metabolism.

Name: TAPIOCA STARCH
Description: Tapioca Starch is a starch obtained from tapioca. It consists primarily of amylose andamylopectin.

Name: CENTELLA ASIATICA (GOTU KOLA) EXTRACT
Description: Extract of the leaves and roots of the medicinal plant Gotu Kola, Centella asiatica.

Name: SODIUM GLUCONATE
Description: Sodium Gluconate is a sodium salt of gluconic acid.

Name: VP/ VA COPOLYMER
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic vinyl polymer composed of vinyl acetate and vinylpyrrolidone.

Name: VANILLIN
Description: Vanillin is a substituted aromatic aldehyde.

Name: DICALCIUM PHOSPHATE
Description: Dicalcium Phosphate is an inorganic salt.

Name: HEXYL LAURATE
Description: Hexyl laurate is composed of hexyl alcohol and lauric acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid

Name: CARRAGEENAN
Description: Carrageenan is a gelatinous polysaccharide material obtained from red seeweed (marine algae).

Name: PUNICA GRANATUM (POMEGRANATE) FRUIT EXTRACT
Description: Extract of the pomegranate fruit.

Name: SODIUM POLYACRYLATE
Description: Sodium Polyacrylate is a sodium salt of Polyacrylic Acid (q.v.).

Name: HYDROLYZED WHEAT PROTEIN
Description: This ingredient is produced by acid or enzymatic hydrolysis of wheat protein.

Name: BUTYLENE/ ETHYLENE/ STYRENE COPOLYMER
Description: Butylene/Ethylene/Styrene Copolymer is a polymer of butylene, ethylene and styrenemonomers terminated by hydrogenation.

Name: CI 45380 (D&C Red No. 21 or 22)
Description: D&C Red 21 is a synthetic dye produced from petroleum or coal tar sources; this dye is FDA-approved for use in pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

Name: SODIUM STEARATE
Description: Sodium salt of stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: ELAEIS GUINEENSIS (AFRICAN OIL PALM) OIL
Description: Oil obtained from African oil palm, Elaeis guineensis.

Name: HYDROLYZED KERATIN
Description: Hydrolyzed Keratin is a hydrolysate of keratin derived by acid, enzyme or other method ofhydrolysis.

Name: CANANGA ODORATA (YLANG YLANG) FLOWER OIL
Description: Oil obtained from the flowers of the ylang-ylang tree Cananga odorata.

Name: ACACIA SENEGAL GUM
Description: This gum is prepared from the dried, sap of the acacia tree, Acacia senegal.

Name: HOMOSALATE
Description: Homosalate is a common sunscreen ingredient. Research indicates it is a weak hormone disruptor, and sunlight breaks down the chemical into harmful byproducts.

Name: VP/ EICOSENE COPOLYMER
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic polymer of a hydrocarbon eicosene and vinylpyrrolidone.

Name: SODIUM METHYL COCOYL TAURATE
Description: Sodium Methyl Cocoyl Taurate is a sodium salt of the coconut fatty acid amide ofN-methyltaurine.

Name: GLYCOL STEARATE
Description: Glycol Stearate is composed ethylene glycol and stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: SORBITAN OLEATE
Description: Sorbitan Oleate is a monoester of oleic acid and hexitol anhydrides derived from sorbitol.

Name: ISOPROPYL TITANIUM TRIISOSTEARATE
Description: This ingredient is a synthetic compound based on stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: C13-14 ISOPARAFFIN
Description: C13-14 Isoparaffin is a mixture of hydrocarbons (mineral oils) derived from petroleum.

Name: POLYACRYLAMIDE
Description: Polyacrylamide is a synthetic polymer of acrylamide.

Name: BENZOPHENONE-1
Description: Benzophenone-1 is a benzene-based UV absorber.

Name: SODIUM SULFATE
Description: Sodium Sulfate is an inorganic salt.

Name: BENTONITE
Description: Bentonite is a native hydrated colloidal aluminum silicate clay. This ingredient is not anapproved colorant for the US. To identify the colorant allowed for use in the European Union (EU), theINCI Name CI 77004 must be used, except for hair d ye products.

Name: HYDROFLUOROCARBON 152A
Description: Hydrofluorocarbon 152a is a halocarbon.

Name: SODIUM ASCORBYL PHOSPHATE
Description: This ingredient is a salt of ascorbic acid (Vitamin C), used as an antioxidant.

Name: OENOTHERA BIENNIS (EVENING PRIMROSE) OIL
Description: Evening Primrose oil is extracted from Oenothera biennis, a plant native to North America.

Name: ZINGIBER OFFICINALE (GINGER) ROOT EXTRACT
Description: Zingiber Officinale (Ginger) Root Extract is an extract of the roots of the ginger, Zingiberofficinale.

Name: PEG-60 HYDROGENATED CASTOR OIL
Description: PEG-60 Hydrogenated Castor Oil is a polyethylene glycol derivative of Hydrogenated CastorOil (q.v.) with an average of 60 moles of ethylene oxide.

Name: DIPOTASSIUM GLYCYRRHIZATE
Description: Dipotassium Glycyrrhizate is a dipotassium salt of Glycyrrhizic Acid (q.v.).

Name: PROPANE
Description: Propane is a hydrocarbon.

Name: SORBITAN STEARATE
Description: Sorbitan stearate is a surfactant composed of sweetener sorbitol and stearic acid, a naturally occurring fatty acid.

Name: DICAPRYLYL CARBONATE
Description: Dicaprylyl Carbonate is a diester of carbonic acid and caprylyl alcohol.

Name: LAURIC ACID
Description: Lauric acid is a naturally occurring fatty acid common in coconut oil.

Name: LANOLIN
Description: Lanolin is a refined derivative of the fat-like sebaceous secretion of sheep. This ingredient is listed in the PETA's Caring Consumer guide as an animal-sourced product.

Name: MAGNESIUM CHLORIDE
Description: Magnesium Chloride is an inorganic salt.

Name: SODIUM LAUROYL SARCOSINATE
Description: Synthetic skin conditioning agent.

Name: CETYL ETHYLHEXANOATE
Description: Cetyl Ethylhexanoate is an ester of cetyl alcohol and 2-ethylhexanoic acid.

Name: TROMETHAMINE
Description: Tromethamine is an aliphatic compound.

Name: STEVIA REBAUDIANA (SWEETLEAF) EXTRACT
Description: Stevia Rebaudiana Extract is an extract of the aerial parts of Stevia rebaudiana.

Name: DIAZOLIDINYL UREA (FORMALDEHYDE RELEASER)
Description: Diazolidinyl urea is an antimicrobial preservative that works by forming formaldehyde in cosmetic products. People exposed to such formaldehyde-releasing ingredients may develop a formaldehyde allergy or an allergy to the ingredient itself. In the U.S. approximately 20% of cosmetics and personal care products contain a formaldehyde-releaser and the frequency of contact allergy to these ingredients is much higher among Americans compared to studies in Europe.

Name: HYDROGENATED STYRENE/ ISOPRENE COPOLYMER
Description: Hydrogenated Styrene/Isoprene Copolymer is an end product of the controlled hydrogenationof Styrene/Isoprene Copolymer (q.v.).

Name: MAGNESIUM MYRISTATE
Description: Magnesium Myristate is a magnesium salt of myristic acid.

Name: LACTOBACILLUS FERMENT
Description: Lactobacillus Ferment is an extract of the product resulting from the fermentation ofLactobacillus.

Name: GLYCOLIC ACID
Description: Gylcolic acid is an alpha hydroxy acid; used in chemical peels and anti-aging skin products; can irritate skin.

Name: BUTANE
Description: Butane is a hydrocarbon.

Name: PPG-9
Description: PPG-9 is a polymer of propylene oxide.

Name: POLYGLYCERYL-3 POLYRICINOLEATE
Description: Polyglyceryl-3 Polyricinoleate is a complex ester of Polyglycerin-3 (q.v.) and a polymer ofRicinoleic Acid (q.v.).

Name: SODIUM COCOATE
Description: Sodium cocoate is the sodium salt of fatty acids from coconut oil; lauric acid is the primary component of this oil.

Name: HYDROXYPROPYL METHYLCELLULOSE
Description: Hydroxypropyl methylcellulose is a semisynthetic polymer based on cellulose.

Name: HYDROLYZED GLYCINE SOJA (SOY) PROTEIN
Description: This ingredient is produced by acid or enzymatic hydrolysis of soy protein.

Name: TRIDECETH-12

Long-term, high-volume occupational exposure has been also linked to other disorders such as progressive systemic sclerosis, systemic lupus erythematosus, rheumatoid arthritis, dermatomyositis, glomerulonephritis (renal disease) and vasculitis. Research is ongoing on the relevance of these systemic effects to silica exposure in non-occupational settings via consumer products (Steenland 2005; Stratta 2001).

Name: CYANOCOBALAMIN (VITAMIN B12)

Cyanocobalamin is a synthetic form of vitamin B12 most commonly found in dietary supplements and prescription medications. Name: ISOBUTYLPARABEN
Description: Isobutylparaben is in the parabens family of preservatives used by the food, pharmaceutical, and personal care product industries. Parabens mimic estrogen, are potential hormone (endocrine) system disruptors, and were found in the breast cancer tumors of 19 of 20 women studied (Darbre 2004). The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) tested urine from a group of 2,548 Americans over the age of 6 and found parabens in over 99% of samples (Calafat 2010). Isobutylparaben is closely related to butylparaben, a compound considered to be a potential human endocrine system disruptor by the European Commission on Endocrine Disruption (EU 2007). Isobutylparaben appears to be more strongly estrogenic than butylparaben (Darbre 2002, Vo 2010), but receives a lower hazard score in Skin Deep because of the limited amount of toxicological research on this chemical. Subsequent research and agency assessments may find isobutylparaben to be as or more hazardous to the endocrine system than butylparaben.

Name: FORMALDEHYDE
Description:
Formaldehyde is a carcinogenic impurity released by a number of cosmetic preservatives, including diazolidinyl urea, imidazolidinyl urea, DMDM hydantoin, quaternium-15, 2-bromo-2-nitropropane-1,3-diol, and sodium hydroxylmethylglycinate. According to reviews by the industry-funded Cosmetic Ingredient Review panel, these cosmetic ingredients can release formaldehyde at levels as high as one-tenth that of the original ingredient (CIR 2006). Successful treatment of formaldehyde-triggered contact allergic dermatitis through substitution of body care products free of these preservatives (Flyvholm 1992) is implicit confirmation of the presence of low levels of formaldehyde in these products.

The International Agency for Research on Carcinogens (IARC) has classified formaldehyde as 'carcinogenic to humans,' and the U.S. National Toxicology Program has classified it as 'reasonably anticipated to be a human carcinogen,' based on emerging evidence in humans and robust evidence in animals (IARC 2004; NTP 2005). Occupational exposures to formaldehyde gas are linked to nasal and nasopharyngeal cancers (IARC 2004; NTP 2005). Animal studies confirm this link, and also suggest an association between formaldehyde in drinking water and stomach and gastrointestinal cancer and leukemia (NTP 2005).

Despite the considerable health concerns associated with this carcinogen, until recently formaldehyde itself was a common ingredient of nail polish. Consumer pressure has now forced many major cosmetics manufacturers to voluntarily remove this ingredient from their nail products. European health protections now limit the concentration of formaldehyde in cosmetics to 0.2%, and require that body care products containing formaldehyde or formaldehyde-releasing ingredients be labeled with the warning 'contains formaldehyde' if the concentration of formaldehyde in the product exceeds 0.05% (SCCPNP 2002).

Even the industry-funded Cosmetic Ingredient Review panel recommends that cosmetic products not contain more than 0.2% formaldehyde, and does not consider formaldehyde to be safe in aerosol products (CIR 2006). However, as it stands in the U.S. there are no restrictions on the levels of formaldehyde allowed in any body care products, no requirement to test products made with formaldehyde-releasing preservatives for levels of formaldehyde, and certainly no obligation to inform consumers that the products they use each day are likely to contain a cancer-causing chemical that does not appear on the list of ingredients.

References

CIR (Cosmetics Ingredient Review). 2006. 2006 CIR Compendium, containing abstracts, discussions, and conclusions of CIR cosmetic ingredient safety assessments. Washington DC.

Flyvholm MA, Menn T. 1992. Allergic contact dermatitis from formaldehyde. A case study focussing on sources of formaldehyde exposure. Contact Dermatitis. 1992 Jul;27(1):27-36.

IARC (International Agency for Research on Carcinogens). 2004. Formaldehyde. IARC monographs on the evaluation of carcinogenic risks to humans / World Health Organization, International Agency for Research on Cancer 88.

NTP (National Toxicology Program). 2005. National Toxicology Panel 11th Report on Carcinogens: Formaldehyde (Gas). Available: http://ntp.niehs.nih.gov/ntp/roc/eleventh/profiles/s089form.pdf [Accessed August 14, 2008].

SCCPNP (Scientific Committee on Cosmetic Products and Non-food Products). 2002. Opinion concerning a clarification on the formaldehyde and para-formaldehyde entry in Directive 76/768/EEC on cosmetic products. Opinion: European Comission.

Name: ISOPROPYLPARABEN
Description: Isopropylparaben is in the parabens family of preservatives used by the food, pharmaceutical, and personal care product industries. Parabens mimic estrogen, are potential hormone (endocrine) system disruptors, and were found in the breast cancer tumors of 19 of 20 women studied (Darbre 2004). The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) tested urine from a group of 2,548 Americans over the age of 6 and found parabens in over 99% of samples (Calafat 2010). Isopropylparaben is closely related to propylparaben, a compound considered to be a potential human endocrine system disruptor by the European Commission on Endocrine Disruption (EU 2007). Isopropylparaben appears to be more strongly estrogenic than propylparaben (Vo 2010), but receives a lower hazard score in Skin Deep because of the limited amount of toxicological research on this chemical. Subsequent research and agency assessments may find isopropylparaben to be as or more hazardous to the endocrine system than propylparaben.
